You can use [`std::string::find()`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/string/basic_string/find) in a loop, eg:

```c++
int count = 0;
std::string::size_type pos = 0;
while ((pos = s.find(&quot;xxx&quot;, pos)) != std::string::npos)
{
	++count;
	pos += 3;
}
```

Or [`std::search()`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/algorithm/search):

```c++
#include &lt;algorithm&gt;

int count = 0;
std::string sub = &quot;xxx&quot;;
std::string::iterator iter = s.begin();
while ((iter = std::search(iter, s.end(), sub.begin(), sub.end())) != s.end())
{
	++count;
	iter += sub.size();
}
```

