Your package should have a `Document` class in it. Use the JAXB `unmarshal()` method on your xml file to get a Document object: 

    Document doc = JAXB.unmarshal(output, Document.class);

Now, you can do whatever you want and iterate through the data, handle null values, empty strings, strange block positioning, ... 

    doc.getPage().forEach(page -&gt; page.getBlock().forEach(block -&gt; { 
            // your conditions and stuff
    }));

If you need to get JSON later, I suggest you to use the `gson` library from google, which you can get from maven too, to generate a JSON file from your Document object.

    String stringified = gson.toJson(doc);

Good luck on your project !

